newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 647 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 647 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totalled 647 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 71 wheat, 155 corn, 315 soybean, and 106 soymeal futures contracts traded, along with one soybean call and one soybean put option.
The overnight trend for corn was one to 1-1/4 cents per bushel higher, soybeans two to three cents higher, wheat 1/4 cent higher, and soymeal $0.10 a ton higher.
